4 spaces per indentation level

K&R braces

Unless it is EXTREMELY necessary for readability, avoid skipping braces in one-line logic blocks

Classes/Structs: CamelCase

Methods and free functions: lowerCamelCase

Class private data members: _sameAsMethodsWithLeadingUnderscore

Public struct data members: lowerCamelCase

Function parameters should have 'p' prefix, as in `int increment(int pValue)`

My personal quirk: use one space between function definition/declaration and parenthesis (and no space on function call):
void myfunc () {} // declaration
myfunc() // call
// easier to search for calls

Project structure: try to follow this:
http://www.open-std.org/jtc1/sc22/wg21/docs/papers/2018/p1204r0.html

